('reading', NULL, 161, 'Passage 17:\n\nThe Renaissance was a cultural movement that began in Italy in the 14th century and spread throughout Europe over the next few centuries. The term "Renaissance" means "rebirth," referring to the renewed interest in the classical learning and values of ancient Greece and Rome. This period marked a transition from the Middle Ages to modernity and brought significant changes in art, science, literature, and philosophy.\n\nRenaissance art was characterized by realism, perspective, and humanism. Artists such as Leonardo da Vinci, Michelangelo, and Raphael created works that demonstrated a deep understanding of human anatomy and emotion. The development of linear perspective allowed artists to create the illusion of depth on flat surfaces, making paintings appear more realistic than ever before.\n\nThe Renaissance also witnessed remarkable scientific progress. Nicolaus Copernicus challenged the geocentric view of the universe, proposing that the Earth orbited the Sun rather than vice versa. Galileo Galilei made astronomical observations that supported this heliocentric model and developed the scientific method of systematic observation and experimentation. These advances laid the groundwork for the Scientific Revolution.\n\nThe invention of the printing press by Johannes Gutenberg around 1440 had a profound impact on the Renaissance. Books became more affordable and accessible, facilitating the spread of knowledge and ideas. This technological innovation contributed to increased literacy rates and helped disseminate Renaissance ideals throughout Europe.\n\nWhat is the main topic of the passage?', 'Italian history', 'The characteristics and impacts of the Renaissance', 'The life of Leonardo da Vinci', 'Medieval European art', 'b'),
